Class MergeShuffle

  • java.lang.Object
    • o6167656e74323431.stupidjava.MergeShuffle

  • public final class MergeShuffle
extends java.lang.Object
    This class provides an O(n*log(n)) method for shuffling arrays using merge-sort as a framework for the algorithm.
    Version:
    1.2
    Author:
    6167656e74323431

      • shuffleArray

        public static <T> T[] shuffleArray(T[] target)
        Function that uses a merge-sort style algorithm to sort an array of numbers. This function does not do the operations in place, instead it returns a shuffled copy of the original array.
        Parameters:
        target - The original version of this array that will be copied, and then shuffled.
        Returns:
        A shuffled copy of the original array.
